From: Murray S. Kucherawy <msk@trusteddomain.org>
To: opendmarc-announce@trusteddomain.org, opendmarc-users@trusteddomain.org
Subject: OpenDMARC v1.1.3 released

The Trusted Domain Project is pleased to announce the availability of
OpenDMARC v1.1.3, now available for download from SourceForge.

This is a bug fix release that fixes one API bug and also corrects some
issues with reporting of SPF results.  Upgrade is recommended.

The full RELEASE_NOTES for this version, showing changes since the last
release:

1.1.3		2013/04/13
	Fix reporting of nonexistent SPF results.  Problem noted by
		Andrei Ioachim.
	Fix extraction of data from Received-SPF.  Problem noted by
		Todd Lyons.
	LIBOPENDMARC: Fix bug #47: Make sure that
		opendmarc_policy_fetch_utilized_domain() returns the
		organizational domain if that's the domain whose policy
		was selected.  Reported by John Mears.

Please use the mailing lists at http://www.trusteddomain.org/ to report
problems, make suggestions, or ask questions.  The ticketing system at
SourceForge is not yet available for general use by the community.

The Trusted Domain Project
